</div><br />
<div class="newblue-con-quote-box"><a name="answer-id-007688"></a>
<div class="newblue-editortext" style="text-align:left">Janet Lapey, MD, Executive Director of Concerned Citizens for Drug Prevention, Inc., stated the following in her Oct. 1, 1997 statement to the Subcommittee on Crime of the Committee on the Judiciary in the House of Representatives:</div><br />
<div class="newblue-quote-indent">
<div class="newblue-editortext" style="text-align:left">"Marijuana is not the safe drug portrayed by the marijuana lobby. It is addictive; it adversely affects the immune system; leads to the use of other drugs such as cocaine; is linked to cases of cancer; causes respiratory diseases, mental disorders, including psychosis, depression, panic attacks, hallucinations, paranoia, decreased cognitive performance, disconnected thought, delusions, and impaired memory."</div><br />
<span>
Oct. 1, 1997 - <a href="/view.source.php?sourceID=003541" alt="Janet Lapey, MD" title="Janet Lapey, MD" target="_blank">Janet Lapey, MD&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i></a><br />
