</div><br />
<div class="newblue-con-quote-box"><a name="answer-id-007853"></a>
<div class="newblue-editortext" style="text-align:left">Eric A. Voth, MD, Chairman of the Institute on Global Drug Policy, wrote the following in a Nov. 2001 editorial titled "Guidelines for Prescribing Medical Marijuana," published in the <i>Western Journal of Medicine</i>:</div><br />
<div class="newblue-quote-indent">
<div class="newblue-editortext" style="text-align:left">"Physicians should remember that marijuana remains a schedule I drug, that it has not been approved as safe and efficacious by the Food and Drug Administration, and that the use of marijuana by patients holds inherent risk. We do not support recommending the medicinal use of marijuana."</div><br />
<span>
Nov. 2001 - <a href="/view.source.php?sourceID=000301" alt="Eric A. Voth, MD" title="Eric A. Voth, MD" target="_blank">Eric A. Voth, MD&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i><i class="fas fa-star pcstar"></i></a><br />
</span>
